\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset Formula $A\coloneqq\sigma\left(\left\{ (-\infty,r]\mid r\in\mathbb{Q}\right\} \right)=\mathcal{B}\left(\mathbb{R}\right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
First, the Borel set of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 is the 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma-algebra$
\end_inset

 generated by all open set in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $(-\infty,r]^{C}=(r,\infty)$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $A\subset\mathcal{B}\left(\mathbb{R}\right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Second, by the dense property of rational numbers, 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma\left(\left\{ (-\infty,r]\mid r\in\mathbb{Q}\right\} \right)=\sigma\left(\left\{ (-\infty,r]\mid r\in\mathbb{R}\right\} \right)=\sigma\left(\left\{ (a,b]\mid a,b\in\mathbb{R}\right\} \right)=\sigma\left(\left\{ (a,b)\mid a,b\in\mathbb{R}\right\} \right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Now we use the Lemma 2, proved in Homework 2, that any open set in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 is a countable union of open interval, we have the last set in the previous
 chain of equality to be equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}(\mathbb{R})$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem
